import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='ret', kde=True, color='blue', bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily returns?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Daily Returns")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='open', y='close', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Open Price')
    plt.ylabel('Close Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_daily_return = data.groupby('signal')['ret'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='signal', y='ret', data=avg_daily_return)
    
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.2f'),
                       (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()),
                       ha='center', va='baseline',
                       size=12, xytext=(0, 5),
                       textcoords='offset points')
    
    plt.title('What is the average daily return for each signal type?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Signal Type')
    plt.ylabel('Average Daily Return')
    plt.legend(title='Signal Types', loc='upper right', labels=avg_daily_return['signal'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
